  "text": "As the figure shows, in the existing method, the quantization errors become larger for deeper layers. It is because the quantization error generated in each layer is propagated and accumulated across layers. We call this accumulated quantization error. The accumulated errors become larger with more aggressive quantization, e.g., 2 bits, and cause poor performance, i.e., 4.8 % drop [CITATION_1] ) from the top-1 accuracy of the full-precision ResNet-50 for ImageNet classification.",
